article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 91, St. Francis, Pa. 84
article.story: TEANECK, N.J. (AP) -- Cameron Tyler scored a game-high 31 points and handed out eight assists as Fairleigh Dickinson beat St. Francis of Pennsylvania 91-84 on Thursday night. Andre Harris added 18 points for the Knights, while Manny Ubilla had 16 and Michael Peeples finished with 11. Chris Perry led the Red Flash with 20 points, while Devin Sweetney added 19 points and a game-high 11 rebounds and Jelani Lawrence had 16. Tyler went 10-of-16 from the field and 10-of-13 from the free throw line for the Knights (8-6, 3-0 in Northeast Conference), who led for most of the night. However, they struggled to put away St. Francis (4-12, 1-4), which hit nearly 56 percent of its shots but committed 14 turnovers. FDU finally sealed the win when Tyler and Harris each hit four free throws in the final 41 seconds.
